body:

summary: What did you think of the new Captain Marvel comic?
question: What did you think of the new Captain Marvel comic?
answer:
I quite liked it actually. It’s also got an all female team behind it (writing, colouring, art) which is cool.

I liked the way they opened it with Jess/Carol and I like that they’ve introduced Carol and Jennifer. I liked her interactions with Tony, that she doesn’t take his shit. I think Carol’s stories are at their strongest when she’s got good friendships/personal relationships evolving around her.

I’d really like to see this run delve a lot deeper into the character. I think the Life of Captain Marvel run was good, but I think it was really just to give the character that reintroduction. They didn’t have time to deal with the nuts and bolts of what makes her tick. It’s what I want to see here.

I’ve always quite liked her and Rhodey together so I was happy to see that returned. They haven’t really been given the chance to flesh out their dynamic, so this is kind of the perfect opportunity. Still, I don’t want it to be centre stage. Just let it evolve with the core story.


I also want to see a lot more of her relationship with Jess. They’re the best.

summary:
Avengers: Scents
Tony: Eucalyptus (FROM ALL HIS STRESS), his favorite cologne, new tailored suit, shoe polish, hair gel. 
Thor:...
body:
Avengers: Scents

Tony: Eucalyptus (FROM ALL HIS STRESS), his favorite cologne, new tailored suit, shoe polish, hair gel.

Thor: Rainstorm, campfire smoke, slightly of static electricity, musk.

Loki: Slightly smells of copper, hints of mint, old books, clean soap.

Bruce: Old books, marshmallows, hand sanitizer, fresh and clean, probably the original OldSpice.

Steve: Ocean air, slight cologne, fresh linen, clean,

Bucky: Cool breeze, wintergreen gum, berries, the ocean.

Peter Parker: Bubblegum, Mountain Dew, fresh baked bread for Delmar’s, used erasers.

Clint: Sharp cologne, sawdust, fire, iron, pine trees.

Vision: Synthetic fibers, metal, cinnamon, patchouli.

Natasha: Red berries (strawberry, raspberries, cherries), finely aged wine, gunpowder, lilac.

Wanda: Cinnamon and ginger, floral perfume, nail polish.

Pietro: Tic-Tacs, new shoes, hair dye, hair gel, mist after ran, a cold morning.

summary: Sorry for the rant but Benedict haters drain me. Like you see them posting things like oh Doctor Strange is so cool but too bad...
body:
Sorry for the rant but Benedict haters drain me. Like you see them posting things like oh Doctor Strange is so cool but too bad Benedict sucks. I mean, do you still believe in those fake news?

IT HAS BEEN 9 FUCKING YEARS AND YOU’RE STILL MAKING JOKES WITH HIS NAME!! IT’S NOT FUNNY ANYMORE, HOLY CRAP!!! STOP REPEATING WHAT MEDIA MADE FUN OF ALMOST A DECADE AGO, IT’S LOW TO MOCK SOMEONE BECAUSE OF THEIR NAME AND THEIR LOOKS.

He’s a feminism supporter, he donates MILLIONS to charity, he supports immigrants, he participated tons of fund raising programs WHAT ELSE DO YOU WANT?? Do you still believe in the fucking lies? Enter freaking Wikipedia and read the fucking facts about him.

If Benedict was a bastard, he would have been taken down at this point, like all the directors and actors who are being sued or fired, because soooo many people hate him because of his activism that ONLY ONE LITTLE SLIP would have been more than enough for all the media to fuck his image for the entire world to see and Disney, no way they would hire him.

JUST RESEARCH BENEDICT ONLINE AND YOU’LL SEE THE FACT ABOUT HIM, AND YOU’LL SEE HOW ALL THE WEBSITES THAT CLAIM HE’S A RACIST, MISOGYNIST OR WHATEVER ARE IMMENSELY VAGUE, TAKING HIS LINES OUT OF CONTEXT JUST TO CLICKBAIT.

If you still don’t believe me, look at HOW MANY LIES ARE OUT THERE ABOUT ROBERT DOWNEY JUNIOR. Do you believe the lies? Are you his hater too? Because man, there are SO MANY FAKE NEWS ABOUT HIM .
